ck, and Iran will be paralyzed and decide not to retaliate for fear of a vastly more devastating nuclear attack. In the short term, the U.S. will succeed, leaving no Iranian nuclear program, civilian or otherwise. Iran will no longer threaten Israel, a regime change will ensue, and a pro-Western government will emerge. However, </span>**<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">__<span style="background: yellow;">even in the best-case scenario</span>__</span>**__, the long-term consequences are dire. **<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="background: yellow;">The nuclear threshold will have been crossed</span></span>** by a nuclear superpower against a non-nuclear country. **<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">Many more countries will rush to get their own nuclear weapons</span>** as a deterrent. With no taboo against the use of nuclear weapons, **<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">they will certainly be used again</span>**. **<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="background: yellow;">Nuclear conflicts will </span>occur</span>**__<span style="font-size: 7pt;"> within the next 10 to 20 years, </span>**<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">__and will <span style="background: yellow;">escalate until much of the world is destroyed</span>__</span>**<span style="font-size: 7pt;">. Let us remember that </span>**<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">__<span style="background: yellow;">the destructive power</span>__</span>** __of existing nuclear arsenals **<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="background: yellow;">is</span></span>**__<span style="font-size: 7pt;"> approximately one million times that of the Hiroshima bomb, </span>**<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">__<span style="background: yellow;">enough to erase Earth's population many times over</span>__</span>**<span style="font-size: 7pt;">. </span> </span></span>
